$lang['The hexadecimal system is a base 16 number notation, while the decimal system is a base 10 number notation. In other words, the hexadecimal system uses 16 symbols to represent numbers, while the decimal system uses 10 symbols. This expansion also allows for a higher information density-hexadecimal digits can represent twice as many values as decimal digits.'] = 'Isixokelelwano se-hexadecimal sisiseko se-16 sobhalo lwamanani, ngelixa inkqubo yedesimali isisiseko se-10 inani lobhalo. Ngamanye amazwi, inkqubo ye-hexadecimal isebenzisa iisimboli ezili-16 ukumela amanani, ngelixa inkqubo yedesimali isebenzisa iisimboli ezili-10. Olu lwando lukwavumela ulwazi oluphezulu loxinaniso-hexadecimal amanani angamela amaxabiso aphindwe kabini njengedesimali.';
$lang['Hexadecimal numbers are made up of 16 digits instead of the 10 in a decimal number. The order of these numbers starts over after F (or 15 in decimal), while it doesn’t in the decimals. Check out the table below to see how they compare!'] = 'Amanani anehexadecimal enziwe ngamanani ali-16 endaweni ye-10 kwinani lokugqibela. Ulandelelwano lwala manani luqala ngaphaya emva kuka-F (okanye i-15 kwidesimali), ngelixa ingekho kwiidesimali. Jonga le theyibhile ingezantsi ukuze ubone ukuba zithelekisa njani!';
$lang['How do you convert a Hexadecimal to a Decimal?'] = 'Uyiguqula njani iHexadecimal ukuya kwiDesimali?';
$lang['When converting hexadecimal to decimal, the first step is to divide the hex number by 16. This will give you the base number. The second step is to divide each digit of the hex number by 16 and write down the results. Finally, add up all of the numbers that were just calculated.'] = 'Xa uguqula ihexadecimal ukuya kwidesimali, inyathelo lokuqala kukwahlula inani lehex ngo 16. Oku kuyakukunika inani lesiseko. Inyathelo lesibini kukwahlula idijithi nganye yenombolo ye-hex ngo-16 kwaye ubhale phantsi iziphumo. Ekugqibeleni, dibanisa onke amanani asandula kubalwa.';
$lang['For example, if someone wants to convert 9F7A to decimal, they would first divide 9F7A by 16 which equals 6051. Then they would divide each digit of 6051 by 16 which equals 381. Lastly, they would add up 381 + 381 + 381 which equals 1144. Therefore, 9F7A in decimal is equal to 1144'] = 'Umzekelo, ukuba umntu ufuna ukuguqula u 9F7A abe kwidesimali, bazakwahlula kuqala u 9F7A ngo 16 olingana no 6051. Bazakwahlula ke inani ngalinye lika 6051 ngo 16 elilingana no 381. Okokugqibela, bazakudibanisa 381 + 381 + 381 elilingana 1144. Ngoko ke, 9F7A ngokwedesimali ilingana no-1144';
$lang['How do you convert a Decimal to a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Uyiguqula njani idesimali ibe yiHexadecimal?';
$lang['Converting decimal to hexadecimal is a simple process, and can be done with a calculator or online converter. In order to convert the number, divide it by 16 and take the remainder. This remainder will then correspond to a hexadecimal digit. For example, if you have the decimal number 234, divide it by 16 and take the remainder: 234 / 16 = 14 R 2. Therefore, in hexadecimal notation, this number would be written as “E2”.'] = 'Ukuguqula idesimali ibe yi-hexadecimal yinkqubo elula, kwaye inokwenziwa ngekhaltyhuleyitha okanye isiguquleli se-intanethi. Ukuze uguqule inani, yahlule ngo-16 kwaye uthathe intsalela. Le ntsalela iya kuthi emva koko ingqinelane nenani le-hexadecimal. Umzekelo, ukuba unenani lokugqibela elingu-234, lahlule ngo-16 kwaye uthathe intsalela: 234/16 = 14 R 2. Ngoko ke, kubhalo lwe-hexadecimal, eli nani lingabhalwa njengo-“E2”.';
$lang['There are many tools available online that can help with converting between decimal and hexadecimal numbers. Additionally, most calculators have a built-in function that will allow you to do this conversion very easily. With just a few clicks of the mouse or taps on the keyboard, you’ll be able to change any decimal value into its corresponding hexadecimal equivalent!'] = 'Zininzi izixhobo ezikhoyo kwi-intanethi ezinokunceda ekuguquleni phakathi kwedesimali kunye namanani e-hexadecimal. Ukongeza, uninzi lweekhaltyhuleyitha lunomsebenzi owakhelwe ngaphakathi oza kukuvumela ukuba wenze olu guqulelo ngokulula kakhulu. Ngokucofa nje okumbalwa kwemouse okanye ukucofa ibhodi yezitshixo, uya kuba nakho ukutshintsha naliphi na ixabiso ledesimali ukuya kukulingana kwayo nehexadecimal ehambelanayo!';
$lang['What are the benefits of using a Hexadecimal over a Decimal?'] = 'Ziziphi iingenelo zokusebenzisa i-Hexadecimal ngaphezu kweDesimali?';
$lang['The hexadecimal, or base-16, system was designed to emulate some of the same properties as the decimal system. In other words, it was created to make things easier for us humans. The number 423 has 16 digits instead of 10 digits available in a decimal system. This is because hexadecimal uses a base of 16 symbols instead of 10. After F, the order begins again with 0 and so on and so forth until we get to 15 which is notated as F.'] = 'I-hexadecimal, okanye i-base-16, inkqubo yayiyilwe ukulinganisa ezinye iimpawu ezifanayo njengenkqubo yokugqibela. Ngamanye amazwi, yayidalelwe ukwenza izinto zibe lula kuthi bantu. Inani elingu-423 linamanani ali-16 endaweni yamadijithi ali-10 akhoyo kwinkqubo yesishumi. Oku kungenxa yokuba i-hexadecimal isebenzisa isiseko seesimboli ezili-16 endaweni ye-10. Emva kuka-F, ulandelelwano luqala kwakhona ngo-0 njalo njalo njalo njalo de sifike ku-15 ephawulwe njengo-F.';
$lang['Hexadecimal encoding reduces the number of digits by a factor of eight when compared to the decimal system. Additionally, hexadecimal numbers have an information density that is twice as high as decimal numbers do. So, why should you bother learning this funky little numbering scheme? Because it can make your life easier! When working with digital systems or data transmission, using hex will save you time and energy when decoding cryptic messages or data streams.'] = 'I-encoding ye-hexadecimal inciphisa inani lamadijithi ngomlinganiselo wesibhozo xa kuthelekiswa nedecimal system. Ukongeza, amanani e-hexadecimal anobuninzi bolwazi obuphindwe kabini kunamanani edesimali. Ke, kutheni kufuneka uzikhathaze ngokufunda esi sikimu sihlekisayo samanani amancinci? Kuba inokwenza ubomi bakho bube lula! Xa usebenza ngeesistim zedijithali okanye ukuhanjiswa kwedatha, ukusebenzisa i-hex kuya kongela ixesha namandla xa ucofa imiyalezo efihlakeleyo okanye imijelo yedatha.';
$lang['What are the benefits of using a Decimal over a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Ziziphi iingenelo zokusebenzisa iDesimali ngaphezu kweHexadecimal?';
$lang['When it comes to binary coding, Hexadecimal is more efficient because it reduces 8 digits to 2. Additionally, Hex provides a greater degree of information density and higher accuracy in numbers than binary does. This is due to the fact that Hex uses 16 symbols instead of just two like binary. Because of this increased efficiency, Hexadecimal is often used when binary coding in computing and digital electronics as well as for computer science applications.'] = 'Xa kufikwa kwikhowudi yokubini, iHexadecimal isebenza kakuhle kakhulu kuba inciphisa amadijithi ayi-8 ukuya ku-2. Ukongeza, iHex ibonelela ngeqondo elikhulu loxinaniso lolwazi kunye nokuchaneka okuphezulu kwamanani kunendlela yokubini. Oku kungenxa yokuba i-Hex isebenzisa iisimboli ezili-16 endaweni yezimbini ezifana nokubini. Ngenxa yoku kunyuswa kokusebenza kakuhle, iHexadecimal isoloko isetyenziswa xa kukho ikhowudi yokubini kwikhompyuter nakwi-elektroniki yedijithali nakwizicelo zesayensi yekhompyuter.';
$lang['In addition, Hexadecimal takes up less space than decimal. With only two digits instead of 8 binary digits, Hex numbers represent large numbers much more concisely. This can be very helpful when working with computer systems, as there is less chance for mistakes when typing in hex codes compared to decimal codes which have so many decimal points all over the place!'] = 'Ukongeza, i-Hexadecimal ithatha indawo encinci kunedesimali. Ngamadijithi amabini kuphela endaweni ye-8 yokubini amanani, amanani e-Hex amele amanani amakhulu ngakumbi ngokufutshane. Oku kunokuba luncedo kakhulu xa usebenza ngeenkqubo zekhompyuter, njengoko mancinci amathuba eempazamo xa uchwetheza kwiikhowudi ze-hex xa kuthelekiswa neekhowudi zedesimali ezinamanqaku amaninzi kwindawo yonke!';
$lang['What is the range of values that can be represented by a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Loluphi uluhlu lwamaxabiso olunokumelwa yi-Hexadecimal?';
$lang['A hexadecimal number is a number that uses 16 digits instead of the 10 digits we use in the decimal system. This number system is called base-16, and it helps us to emulate the properties of our familiar decimal system. In hexadecimal, each digit represents a power of 16. The numbers 0 through 9 represent the powers of 1 through 10, while A through F represent the powers of 11 through 15.'] = 'Inani elinehexadecimal linani elisebenzisa amanani ali-16 endaweni yamanani ali-10 esiwasebenzisayo kwinkqubo yokugqibela. Le nkqubo yamanani ibizwa ngokuba yi-base-16, kwaye isinceda ukuba sixelise iimpawu zesixokelelwano sethu esiqhelekileyo sedesimali. Kwi-hexadecimal, idijithi nganye imele amandla ka-16. Amanani u-0 ukuya ku-9 amele amagunya ka-1 ukuya ku-10, ngoxa u-A ukuya ku-F umele amagunya ka-11 ukuya ku-15.';
$lang['Just like in decimal, after 16 symbols have been used in Hexadecimal, the order of numbers starts over again at zero. So, hexadecimal 10 is equal to decimal 16, and hexadecimal 11 is equal to decimal 17. And so on!'] = 'Kanye njengakwidesimali, emva kokuba iisimboli ezili-16 zisetyenzisiwe kwi-Hexadecimal, ukulandelelana kwamanani kuqala kwakhona ngo-zero. Ngoko ke, ihexadecimal 10 ilingana nedesimali 16, kwaye ihexadecimal 11 ilingana nedesimali 17. Kwaye njalo!';
